They made me take an MPT Class (Video Editing!?) for a 3d Computer Arts Major?! i found out others in the same major as me didn't have to take it.  COMPLETELY RANDOM!<br>
i hated the school, but i have my reasons, it's because of the person that i am.  <br>
1. I expected it to be a different place than it actually is: (Clean, more Computers around, more interactive environment, more creating your own creations) I expected to have lots of people just like me, into Anime, maybe even games maybe even cars whatever the hell that's fun.  There were just a lotta lame-o's around.. most people were around 4 years older than me (they were 22) and as an example, i had to listen to a discussion about He-Man's sword and Skeletor's sword on a bus ride home.  Needless to say, i never took their bus again.<br>
2. i HATE downtown and i HATE BART.  i had to take bart cuz i live 15 miles from BART.  You're gonna be around Market St., lotsa hobos, damn dirty, rude people everywhere, etc.  Don't pay attention to most of the hobos they're not hungry; i had to learn that the hard way.  And trust me they can get their own food.<br>
3. that video editing class taught some fun skills but for a SIX hour class that can easily be shortened to at least TWO hours and a Teacher who's english i can barely understand.. it SUCKED.<br>
4. This is not so bad but just so you know, they WILL change the way you draw.  I've drawn all my life on simple paper and with my hand down and a mechanical pencil.  Prepare to work with charcoal (my enemy!) and prepare to draw with your whole shoulder, holding your pencil vertically.<br>
My advice, Do yourself a favor and try to go INTO classes in session to check it out.  At least look from the hallway.  The tour they provide doesn't EVEN show how classes are; they'll show you things such as lab rooms, and equipment.  it's much more different than that.  Don't expect the damn school to be so clean or anything even with all the money you pay them.  <br>
If you have your life pretty much dedicated to art right now, i think you could do pretty well, but beware.. some people there have some MAD skill and sometimes their homework will blow yours to hell.  I've spent 4 hours in a lab doing my homework and ended up with some pretty crappy results.<br>
Bah, u know what, if u have more questions about hte place i'd be happy to answer them.  my AIM Screen Name is do0dleboi.  <br>
i also don't attend the school anymore, but don't worry.. i'm not too narrow minded. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=doodleboi>doodle boi</A> at: 11/26/02 8:03:47 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeron30>ZeroN30</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/26/02 10:57:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11409.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://zeron30.hypermart.net/images/drunkemon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help</span><hr size=1>      Something also to consider is when you pick your major, look to see what courses are included in your program. For example my  major is Media Arts and Animation which focuses on animation 2d and 3d but at the same time I'm covering traditional media, illustration, design (graphic to character), a little archetecture, color theory, and a crap load of computer programs I cant even spell let alone use yet, Flash, Maya, AfterAffects, 3d max, and even buisness software, and that isnt including what I get to learn on Mac.<br>
<br>
      Also check to see if they have internships, or job placement. I'm looking into an internship at HI*FI right now, but I know like Cal Arts (tough school, but good) has internships at Disney. Your best bet is to shop around and get as much info as you can. Best wishes.<br>
